{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"wispy-cheerless-tick","description":"# Persist ticket digest as a content-hash-keyed record on the ticket (shared cache)\n\n## Why\nThe digest is a billable LLM artifact we never want to recompute. Storing it in the SHARED store (auto-pushed) makes one client's enrichment a cache-hit for every other client. Keying by a content-hash lets the cache self-invalidate when the ticket's text drifts — exactly how the kind-keyed `attestations` map computes validity on read (ADR 0009).\n\n## What\nAn event + reducer projection that attaches the digest to a ticket as a content-hash-keyed derived record, mirroring the attestations machinery (`src/rebar/reducer/_present.py:53`, `src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py:395`, `src/rebar/llm/plan_review/attest.py`). Validity (\"is this digest current for the ticket's text?\") is computed on read from the stored content-hash vs the ticket's current content-hash.\n\n## Scope\n- New derived-record event type (preserved-and-ignored by older clients, per the rollout convention) + reducer projection into ticket state.\n- `show` renders the digest presence + freshness; the raw digest is available to the retrieval code.\n- Content-hash helper over the exact fields fed to enrichment (title + description + comments, normalized).\n- IN scope: event, reducer projection, freshness-on-read, presentation. OUT: producing the digest (S1), enqueuing (S3).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A digest can be written to a ticket via an event and projected into reduced state, keyed by content-hash.\n- [ ] Reading a ticket exposes whether its digest is present AND current (stale when the content-hash no longer matches).\n- [ ] The record is shared via the normal auto-commit/auto-push path (no local-only sidecar).\n- [ ] Older clients preserve-and-ignore the new event type (fsck WARNs on newer-than-binary event types, per the rollout convention).\n- [ ] A re-enrichment overwrites the prior digest for that ticket (idempotent, latest-wins) rather than accumulating.","id":"2d0f-19f2-dd15-4336","parent_id":"bd83-c56f-1f72-4ef2","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Persist ticket digest as a content-hash-keyed record on the ticket (shared cache)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783568199099463001,"uuid":"db7a9fb3-e938-4a44-932f-5c3ba62afa16"}